        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 3:38PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 337 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Brady, and another cluster of strong storms in northern Mason
County. All storms were moving south-southwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brady, Brady Lake, Calf Creek, Katemcy, Camp San Saba, Hext, Camp
Air, The Intersection Of Highway 29 And Ranch Road 1222, and The
Intersection Of Us-190 And Ranch Road 1311.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
